<topic id="grid-navigation">
  <title>Grid Mode Navigation</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Grid editing modes<indexterm>Navigation</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>When you first open a document in <uicontrol>Grid</uicontrol> mode, the content is collapsed.
      Only the root element and its attributes are displayed. An arrow sign (<image
        href="../img/ExpandGrid.png"/>) displayed at the left of the node name indicates that this
      node has child nodes. To display the children, click this arrow sign. To collapse a node,
      click the reverse arrow sign (<image href="../img/CollapseGrid.png"/>). The expand/collapse
      actions can also be invoked with the <uicontrol
        conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/numpad_plus"/> and <uicontrol
        conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/numpad_minus"/> keys, or from the
        <uicontrol>Expand/Collapse</uicontrol> submenu of the contextual menu<ph
        product="author developer editor"> or from <menucascade>
          <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>Grid Expand/Collapse</uicontrol>
        </menucascade></ph>.</p>
    <section id="expandcollapse_submenu">
      <title>Expand/Collapse Submenu</title>
      <p>The following actions are available on the <uicontrol>Expand/Collapse</uicontrol> submenu:<dl>
          <dlentry>
            <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/ExpandAll16.png" id="image_zv1_nf3_5r"/>Expand
                All</uicontrol></dt>
            <dd>Expands the selection and all its children.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry>
            <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/CollapseAll16.png" id="image_dwt_4f3_5r"/>Collapse
                All</uicontrol></dt>
            <dd>Collapses the selection and all its children.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry>
            <dt><uicontrol>Expand Children</uicontrol></dt>
            <dd>Expands all the children of the selection but not the selection.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry>
            <dt><uicontrol>Collapse Children</uicontrol></dt>
            <dd>Collapses all the children of the selection but not the selection.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry>
            <dt><uicontrol>Collapse Others</uicontrol></dt>
            <dd>Collapses all the siblings of the current selection but not the selection.</dd>
          </dlentry>
        </dl></p>
    </section>
    <section id="keyboard_shortcuts">
      <title>Keyboard Shortcuts</title>
      <p>A variety of other keyboard shortcuts are also available in <uicontrol>Grid</uicontrol>
          mode:<table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
          <title>Shortcuts in the <uicontrol>Grid</uicontrol> Mode</title>
          <tgroup cols="2">
            <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*" colsep="1" rowsep="1"/>
            <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.09*" colsep="1" rowsep="1"/>
            <thead>
              <row>
                <entry>Key</entry>
                <entry>Action</entry>
              </row>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <row>
                <entry><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/tab"/></entry>
                <entry>Moves the cursor to the next editable value in a table row.</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/shift_tab"/></entry>
                <entry>Moves the cursor to the previous editable value in a table row.</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/enter"/></entry>
                <entry>Begins editing and lets you insert a new value. Also commits the changes
                  after you finish editing.</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/up_arrow_page_up"
                  /></entry>
                <entry>Navigates toward the beginning of the document.</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/down_arrow_page_down"
                  /></entry>
                <entry>Navigates toward the end of the document.</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/shift"/></entry>
                <entry>Used in conjunction with the navigation keys to create a continuous selection
                  area. </entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl"/></entry>
                <entry>Used in conjunction with the mouse cursor to create discontinuous selection
                  areas.</entry>
              </row>
            </tbody>
          </tgroup>
        </table></p>
      <p>The following key combinations can be used to scroll the grid:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_up_arrow"/> - scrolls the grid
          upwards.</li>
        <li><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_down_arrow"/> - scrolls the
          grid downwards.</li>
        <li><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_left_arrow"/> scrolls the grid
          to the left.</li>
        <li><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_right_arrow"/> scrolls the
          grid to the right.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
